\begin{align*}
4x + 14 &= 8x - 48 \\
14 + 48 &= 8x - 4x \\
62 &= 4x \\
x &= \frac{62}{4} \\
x &= \frac{31}{2}
\end{align*}

Now, to find the value of $2x$, we multiply $x$ by 2.

\begin{align*}
2x &= 2 \cdot \frac{31}{2} \\
